HEADWORD: Titubate
<hw>Tit"u*bate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>titubatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>titubare</ets> to stagger,
totter.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To stumble.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To rock or roll, as a curved body on a
plane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Titubation</ent>⟦br⟧
